label: Measles antibodies, by ELISA
definition: Positive measles titer (>250 IU/L), by ELISA. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.

label: Pertussis antibodies, by ELISA
definition: Positive pertussis titer (>38 IU/L at 7m or >26 IU/L at 15m of age), by ELISA. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.

label: Polio serotype 2 antibodies, by microneutralization
definition: Positive polio serotype 2 titer (>8 U/L), by microneutralization. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.

label: Polio IgG antibodies, by ELISA
definition: Positive polio IgG titer (>10 U/L), by ELISA. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.

label: Rotavirus antibodies, by ELISA
definition: Positive Rotavirus IgA titer (>20 U/mL), by ELISA. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.

label: Tetanus antibodies, by ELISA
definition: Positive tetanus titer (>100 IU/L), by ELISA. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.

label: Polio serotype 1 antibodies, by microneutralization
definition: Positive polio serotype 1 titer (>8 U/L), by microneutralization. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.

definition: Positive polio serotype 3 titer (>8 U/L), by microneutralization. Antibody titers in response to vaccination and/or natural exposure were assessed in blood samples collected at 7 and 15 months of age.
